{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}} {{other uses|Globus (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox Magazine |title = Globus |image_file = Globus naslovnica 13250062471099-naslovna.jpg |image_size = |image_caption = Cover of the 23 December 2011 issue |editor = [[Zdravko Milinović]] |editor_title = Editor |staff_writer = |frequency = Weekly |circulation = 28,000 (2009) |category = [[News magazine]] |company = [[Europapress Holding]] |publisher = 4 Media EPH D.O.O. |firstdate = 13 December 1990 |country = [[Croatia]] |language = [[Croatian language|Croatian]] |website = {{URL|globus.jutarnji.hr}} |issn = 0353-9903 }}
'''''Globus''''' is a [[Croatian language]] weekly [[news magazine]] published in [[Zagreb]], Croatia.
==History and profile== ''Globus'' was started in 1990,<ref name=pec>{{cite web|title=Croatian newspapers and magazines|url=http://www.pecob.eu/flex/cm/pages/ServeBLOB.php/L/EN/IDPagina/1468|work=Pecob|accessdate=11 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=gary>{{cite book|author1=Stjepan Malović|author2=Gary W. Selnow|title=The People, Press, and Politics of Croatia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1Cbu97w3w9YC&pg=PA148|accessdate=14 November 2014|date=1 January 2001|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|isbn=978-0-275-96543-3|page=148}}</ref> having some of its first issues published during the [[Croatian War of Independence]].<ref name=Kol2012/> The founders are [[Ninoslav Pavić|Ninoslav Pavic]], Denis Kuljiš and Zdravko Jurak.<ref name=gary/> The magazine is based in Zagreb.<ref name=pec/><ref name="Kol2012">{{cite book|author=Pål Kolstø|title=Media Discourse and the Yugoslav Conflicts: Representations of Self and Other|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jGNWORa2QccC&pg=PA260|accessdate=21 November 2014|date=28 December 2012|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=978-1-4094-9164-4|page=260}}</ref> It is owned by [[Europapress holding]] (EPH) media group,<ref>{{cite web|author=Stojan de Prato|title=Print Media in Croatia ̶ Destroyed by Tabloidisation and De-Professionalisation|url=http://eu.boell.org/sites/default/files/uploads/2013/12/print_media_in_croatia.pdf|work=Heinrich Boell Foundation|accessdate=11 March 2015}}</ref> one of the largest media publishing companies in the country. ''Globus'' is one of EPH's flagship publication along with ''[[Jutarnji list]]'' daily. The magazine is published by 4 Media EPH d.o.o. on a weekly basis.<ref name=pufac/>
Originally devised as [[tabloid (newspaper format)|tabloid]], it never took an openly chauvinist approach of ''[[Slobodni tjednik]]'' and always tried to give the appearance of objectivity. Gradually, its articles began to deal with shady aspects of privatisation, abuses against ethnic [[Serb]] citizens and other topics not covered by mainstream media in Croatia. As such ''Globus'' is credited for introducing [[investigative journalism]] in Croatia. The magazine covers articles on corruption, [[fraud]], [[abuse of power]] and [[political assassination]]s.<ref name=pufac>{{cite web|title=Globus. Factsheet|url=http://www.publicitas.com/en/home/media-solutions/media-search/media-factsheet-detail/mediadata/globus/?PARAM1=EZDGZ2#.VQCRlWSsXRA|work=Publicitas|accessdate=11 March 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402155939/http://www.publicitas.com/en/home/media-solutions/media-search/media-factsheet-detail/mediadata/globus/?PARAM1=EZDGZ2#.VQCRlWSsXRA|archivedate=2 April 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
In 2009 the circulation of ''Globus'' was 28,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://arhiva.nacional.hr/clanak/70799/smjena-u-globusu-nenada-polimca-na-mjestu-glavnog-urednika-zamijenio-nino-dula |title=Smjena u Globusu: Nenada Polimca na mjestu glavnog urednika zamijenio Nino Đula |language=Croatian |accessdate=14 June 2018 |date=5 November 2009 |archivedate=24 July 2012 |work=[[Nacional (weekly)|Nacional]] |trans-title=Sacking in Globus: Nino Đula replaces Nenad Polimac as the editor in chief |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69OX0Q7Cg?url=http://www.nacional.hr/clanak/70799/smjena-u-globusu-nenada-polimca-na-mjestu-glavnog-urednika-zamijenio-nino-dula |df=dmy }}</ref>
