{{wiktionary|inside job}}
An '''inside job''' is a [[crime]], usually [[larceny]], [[robbery]] or [[embezzlement]], committed by a person with a position of trust who is authorized to access a location or procedure with little or no supervision, e.g., a key [[employee]] or [[Management|manager]]. The perpetrator can also be a former employee who still has specialized knowledge necessary to facilitate the crime.

