[[File:Naples Grape Festival.jpg|thumb|Naples Grape Festival]] [[File:Grape festival wine tent.jpg|thumb|Finger Lakes wine tent participant]] '''Naples Grape Festival''' is an annual [[festival]] in [[Naples (town), New York|Naples]], [[New York (state)|New York]], United States, dedicated to [[grape]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1964/09/13/archives/grape-festival-time-in-the-finger-lakes-area.html|title=Grape Festival Time in the Finger Lakes Area|last=Van Dyne|first=Ed |date=September 13, 1964|work=The New York Times|page =XX3|accessdate=21 December 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mpnnow.com/news/x71883633/Naples-goes-purple|title=Naples goes purple|last=Goldman|first=Dan|date=September 28, 2008|work=Daily Messenger (Canandaigua, NY)|accessdate=21 December 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727154458/http://www.mpnnow.com/news/x71883633/Naples-goes-purple|archivedate=27 July 2011|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_action=doc&p_docid=12A9F2AA1DBA0FC8&p_docnum=7&p_theme=gatehouse&s_site=LNYBB&p_product=LNYBB|title= One-tank trip: Grape Festival |date=September 25, 2004 |work=The Corning Leader|accessdate=21 December 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_action=doc&p_docid=12A9F29C04F885A0&p_docnum=2&p_theme=gatehouse&s_site=LNYBB&p_product=LNYBB |first=Jeffery |last=Smith | title=Thousands flock to Naples to enjoy fruit of the vine|date=September 29, 2003 |work=The Corning Leader (Corning, NY)|accessdate=21 December 2009}}</ref> The town of Naples is in the center of [[Finger Lakes AVA|Finger Lakes American Viticultural Area (AVA)]], a region known for grape-growing and wine making in the [[Finger Lakes]] area of [[Upstate New York]].
The festival, which has been held since 1961, includes arts and crafts vendors, a [[wine-tasting]] tent, food, live music, <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.naplesgrapefest.org/FoodVendors.html|title=Music at the Naples Grape Festival|date=August 27, 2009|work=|accessdate=21 December 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090922210617/http://www.naplesgrapefest.org/FoodVendors.html|archivedate=22 September 2009|df=}}</ref> and a [[grape pie]] contest.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fodors.com/world/north-america/usa/new-york/the-finger-lakes/review-438411.html|title=Fodor's Guide on the Naples Grape Festival|date=|work=|accessdate=21 December 2009}}{{dead link|date=February 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
==Other grape festivals== Grape festivals elsewhere include the [[Turpan Silk Road Grape Festival]] in [[Turpan]], [[Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region]], [[China]] <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.china.org.cn/china/2009-08/27/content_18413373.htm|title=Xinjiang celebrating Grape Festival|date=|work=|accessdate=21 December 2009}}</ref> and the [[Lodi Grape Festival and Harvest Fair]] in [[Lodi, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grapefestival.com/|title=Lodi Grape Festival and Harvest Fair|accessdate=21 December 2009}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Boston wine festival]] *[[Food Network South Beach Wine and Food Festival]] *[[Tallahassee Wine and Food Festival]] *[[San Diego Bay Wine & Food Festival]] *[[Temecula Valley Balloon & Wine Festival]]
