The '''World Scout Winter Games''' is an international [[winter sport]]s event for [[Scouting|Scouts]].
==First World Scout Winter Games== The First World Scout Winter Games was held at [[Kandersteg International Scout Centre]] between February 28 and March 3, 2008. Nine teams, representing eight countries participated. The events included [[cross country skiing]], [[curling]], slalom racing, synchronised skiing and a [[triathlon]]. The overall winners were Sweden, with a team from [[Svenska Scoutrådet]], the Swedish Guide & Scout Council.<ref>{{cite web | title = First Ever World Scout Winter Games held at KISC! | publisher = World Scout Bureau | url = http://www.scout.org/en/information_events/news/2008/first_ever_world_scout_winter_games_held_at_kisc | accessdate =2008-03-17}}</ref>
==2nd World Scout Winter Games== The 2nd World Scout Winter Games were to be held in 2010, also in Kandersteg, but had to be cancelled due to a low number of participating countries.{{cn|date=June 2012}}
